<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="803" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/3248: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1943-11-23T19:00:00-04:00" notBefore="1943-11-22T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received November 23, 1943—7:28
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7389. American interests Far East repatriation. Department’s 2726,
                                November 5. Swiss note November 22 states Gorgé submitted question
                                third exchange [to] Japanese Foreign Office spokesman. <pb facs="0958" n="946" xml:id="pg_946"/> Gorgé telegraphs that his
                                informant, while declaring inability make commitment, directed his
                                attention to fact that possibility third exchange could not be given
                                consideration before clarification certain points concerning
                                treatment Japanese citizens interned United States. Spokesman added
                                that Spanish representative requested undertake Investigation nature
                                of which American Government is informed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>